#: ../../source/collaborate/organize-using-custom-user-groups.rst:7
msgid ""
"Custom groups reduce noise and improve focus by notifying the right "
"people in a channel at the right time, while maintaining transparency for"
" all members in that channel. Custom user groups let you notify up to 256"
" users at a time rather than notifying users individually."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/organize-using-custom-user-groups.rst:9
msgid ""
"For example, perhaps you want to @mention a cross-functional team about a"
" bug fixes needed for an upcoming feature release, without notifying "
"everyone else in the channel. Using a custom group notifies the cross-"
"functional team immediately, while keeping important stakeholders in the "
"loop on the status of the feature release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/organize-using-custom-user-groups.rst:11
msgid ""
"Or perhaps you want to add a group of users to a team and a channel. When"
" you @mention a custom group in a channel, Mattermost prompts you to add "
"anyone from that custom group who isn't already a channel and team "
"member. See the :doc:`invite people to your workspace </collaborate"
"/invite-people>` documentation for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/organize-using-custom-user-groups.rst:13
msgid ""
"Once a custom user group has been created, you can mention that group the"
" same way you @mention another Mattermost member. See the :doc:`mention "
"people in messages </collaborate/mention-people>` documentation for "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/organize-using-custom-user-groups.rst:17
msgid ""
"System admins need to enable this feature. See our :ref:`Mattermost "
"Configuration Settings <configure/site-configuration-settings:enable "
"custom user groups>` documentation for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/organize-using-custom-user-groups.rst:18
msgid ""
"From Mattermost v7.2, system admins can limit who can manage custom user "
"groups through the Custom Group Manager system admin role. See the "
":doc:`delegated granular administration </onboard/delegated-granular-"
"administration>` documentation for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/organize-using-custom-user-groups.rst:19
msgid ""
"The ability to create custom user groups on mobile will be available in a"
" future release. @mentions for custom user groups on mobile work the same"
" as :ref:`LDAP-synced groups <collaborate/mention-people:@groupname>`."
msgstr ""

